# CONTRIBUTING

This document contains information about house-styles, project structure and instructions on how to successfully merge
your pull requests. There are strict rules about how documentation should be updated. There are also robust linting
rules to ensure a clean and consistent code base.

## DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT PREREQUISITES

| Software package          | Vendor                   | Version |
|---------------------------|--------------------------|---------|
| Windows                   | Microsoft                | 11      |
| Visual Studio Code (VSC)  | Microsoft                | 1.96.4  |
| NodeJs                    | The OpenJS Foundation    | 23.6.1  |
| NPM                       | Microsoft (GitHub)       | 11.0.0  |
| Markdown Monster          | WestWind                 | 3.6.2.1 |
| markdownlint (VSC Plugin) | David Anson              | 0.58.2  |
| markdownlint              | David Anson              | 0.37.4  |
| markdownlint-cli2         | David Anson              | 0.17.2  |
| WSL (VSC Plugin)          | Microsoft                | 0.88.5  |
| GitHub Desktop            | Microsoft                | 3.4.15  |
| GIMP                      | GIMP Development Team    | 2.10.38 |


ℹ️ *Some software will be less sensitive to which version you use and others it's more important. Especially for linters
. It is advised you set up your development environment to reflect the exact versions of software listed here.
Periodically later versions will be tested and the table updated.*

## PULL REQUESTS

1. All pull requests must be approved by an administrator before they can be merged with the main branch.

2. All PR's must undergo and pass all automated linting and other code quality checks before a successful merging with the main branch.

3. Documentation has to be completed correctly before a merge with the main branch can occur.

4. 

## CODING STANDARDS

The following code standards should be adhered to at all times. Linting processes are in place to catch code that is out of specification.

⛔ If you do not comply with NGG™ policy you will be challenged and likely rejected at PULL time!.

See. [pull requests.](#pull-requests)

### LANGUAGE AGNOSTIC RULES

1. Thy shalt not use magic numbers without sound justification.
2. Direct pushes to the master branch are strictly prohibited.
3. Thy shall not rely solely on automated pipeline tasks to curate my code and fix my mistakes.
4. All pushes to the master branch must be signed.
5. The change log must be kept up to date at all times.
6. Code must be approached with a modular mindset.
7. Hard coding is not encouraged and must be justified.
8. Braces '{}' should always be placed on their own line.


